{
  "texts": [
    "The more relevant the words, the more \"attention\" they receive.",
    "The result, which may appear unexpected but aligns with the mathematical-statistical principles governing neural networks, is that predicting the next word in text generation occurs stochastically.",
    "However, due to the vast number of computations involved, the output aligns closely with user expectations.",
    "This outcome has seen a continual improvement in appropriateness across various subsequent versions of LLMs, resulting in texts that are increasingly challenging to distinguish from those produced by humans.",
    "From a historical perspective, it's notable that the initial applications of Transformers, as described in the seminal article by Vaswani and colleagues, were related to machine translation-one of the earliest topics addressed in the field of language automation and NLP, with significant attention to linguistic modeling since 2010 (Bahdanau et al. 2014)."
  ]
}